# --- Site ---
# Public site URL (canonical, OG URLs, etc.)
NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://www.floralwhispersgifts.co.ke

# --- Google Business reviews (homepage carousel) ---
# API: Google Cloud "Places API" (legacy) — Place Details.
# 1. Create a project in Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Enable API: "Places API" (Maps Platform → Places API, or APIs & Services → Library → search "Places API").
# 3. Create credentials → API key. Restrict the key (HTTP referrers for browser use is NOT used here;
#    this key is only used server-side in Next.js — prefer "IP addresses" for your server, or use a
#    separate restricted key pattern your host supports).
# 4. Find your Place ID: use https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/places/web-service/place-id
#    or search your business in Google Maps → Share → the link sometimes contains place id, or use
#    the Place ID finder in Google documentation.
#
# Place Details returns at most a small sample of review text (typically up to 5). The listing’s
# overall rating and total review count are also returned and shown in the header.
#
# Prefer storing these in .env.local (gitignored). Server-only — never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ for the key.
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=
# Required for reviews: find Place ID via Google Maps / Place ID finder after billing is enabled.
GOOGLE_PLACE_ID=

# Optional: URL for the "Leave us a Google Review" button (your Google review link / Business Profile).
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_REVIEW_URL=
